This paper is about text classification using neural models, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model that addresses the limitations of existing models, which involves designing a joint input-label embedding with controllable capacity and a joint-space-dependent classification unit. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on multilingual text classification, which may also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) category. Finally, the paper mentions biomedical text classification, which may suggest a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
